id: pm-p5u6
title: "Bound local temp footprint: prune Node compile cache and guarantee smoke/dogfood sandbox cleanup on failure"
description: "ecosystem review 2026-07-06 hit a full /tmp user quota (tmpfs usrquota, EDQUOT) that broke the local agent shell entirely. Post-mortem inventory: pm-cli-node-compile-cache-1000 had grown to 1.7GB (src/cli.ts enableCompileCache never prunes; every build hash accumulates), plus ~2GB of leaked pm-scaffold-review*-smoke-* dirs and 7 pm-changelog-node-cli-* dirs from Jun 29-30 sessions whose scripts mkdtemp'd but did not clean on failure/interrupt. smoke-cleanup.mjs cleanupTempRoot is only wired into smoke-npx-from-pack.mjs."
type: Chore
status: open
priority: 2
tags[5]: "area:cli",dx,perf,scripts,tech-debt
created_at: "2026-07-06T09:04:36.860Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-21T10:52:31.160Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 120
acceptance_criteria: compile-cache dir bounded (stale entries pruned or non-current versions dropped); every mkdtemp-using script cleans its sandbox via try/finally + signal handlers; aborted smoke runs leave no >100MB residue in /tmp
parent: pm-u9d0
risk: low
confidence: high
dependencies[1]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
  pm-j8vq,related,"2026-07-21T07:33:00.706Z",codex-root-20260721,null
comments[16]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-16T15:14:51.889Z",codex-gpt5-root,"PR #573 CI evidence: static quality, package boundary, and all token-budget measurements passed, but final rmSync of /tmp/pm-token-budget-AclN4M hit transient ENOTEMPTY. The same gate passed locally before and after the run; this confirms the existing broader temp-lifecycle chore still owns cleanup retry/signal hardening. No script implementation was added in this review slice because the next PR head naturally reruns the full gate and this item's acceptance criteria also require compile-cache plus every mkdtemp caller, not a one-line partial close."
  "2026-07-21T06:54:35.054Z",codex-root-20260721,"Live GitHub evidence 2026-07-21: Auto Release run 29804774154 / GH-626 failed after all coverage measurements when scripts/release/token-budget-gate.mjs final rmSync hit ENOTEMPTY on /tmp/pm-token-budget-fyfySy under Node 24. Reusing this canonical temp-lifecycle item; no duplicate created."
  "2026-07-21T07:33:06.446Z",codex-root-20260721,"Progress evidence: fixed Auto Release GH-626 by routing token-budget cleanup through the shared resilient retry primitive; consolidated external-package and contracts cleanup; added version-scoped compile-cache generation pruning. Broader every-mkdtemp signal cleanup remains, so this item stays open and is released after this PR slice."
  "2026-07-21T07:39:45.232Z",codex-root-20260721,"Verification evidence: both linked cleanup runs now pass (15 token-budget cleanup tests; 26 compile-cache/shared-cleanup tests across four suites)."
  "2026-07-21T07:45:23.196Z",codex-root-20260721,"Full-suite correction: removed the unnecessary existsSync postcondition from cleanupTempRoot so force-recursive deletion remains compatible with partial fs mocks while retaining outer retry/sweep behavior; synthesized non-Error failures now preserve the original value. All 37 cleanup/script tests pass."
  "2026-07-21T07:54:57.149Z",codex-root-20260721,"Final verification: the public compile-cache generation resolver is directly covered alongside pruning and resilient cleanup; the complete 6045-test coverage suite passes at exactly 100% lines/statements/functions/branches. This PR intentionally leaves the broader every-mkdtemp signal-handler acceptance work open."
  "2026-07-21T08:12:07.571Z",codex-root-20260721,"Greptile remediation: compile-cache pruning now reads string directory entries directly instead of allocating Dirent objects only to discard their type metadata. Focused lifecycle coverage remains green."
  "2026-07-21T08:16:41.647Z",codex-root-20260721,"Final review-head proof: the allocation simplification and resilient cleanup path pass the complete 6052-test suite at exact 100% coverage."
  "2026-07-21T09:10:30.997Z",codex-root-20260721,"Hosted review remediation: compile-cache generation names now reject unsafe filename tokens and pruning retains a bounded fresh-concurrency grace so two pm versions starting together cannot delete one another. A real filesystem race test removes a candidate between readdir and stat; only ENOENT is ignored and all other failures remain visible."
  "2026-07-21T09:15:16.813Z",codex-root-20260721,"Exact remediation-head proof: all 332 test files and 6053 tests pass at 100/100/100/100 coverage. This PR completes bounded, concurrency-safe compile-cache generations and resilient cleanup surfaces, while the remaining every-mkdtemp signal-handler work stays open in this same canonical item."
  "2026-07-21T10:13:36.637Z",codex-root-20260721,"Hosted CI remediation: Windows Node 24 exhausted the prior 375 ms helper retry window with EBUSY on the generated workspace. Test sandboxes now apply Node's recursive rm retry contract plus the same eight-attempt 120 ms backoff used by production cleanup."
  "2026-07-21T10:14:17.179Z",codex-root-20260721,"Hosted CodeRabbit remediation: compile-cache validation now accepts leading underscore and hyphen safe tokens, matching resolveCompileCacheGeneration for scoped package names such as @org/package while continuing to reject dot segments and path separators. Focused SDK and scale-workspace suites pass (10 tests)."
  "2026-07-21T10:29:28.119Z",codex-root-20260721,"Exact final-head proof: 332 test files and 6053 tests pass; compile-cache scoped-package generation and Windows-portable cleanup are covered within 100% statements (40688/40688), branches (28623/28623), functions (8264/8264), and lines (39582/39582)."
  "2026-07-21T10:31:05.390Z",codex-root-20260721,"Installed-package acceptance proof: pnpm smoke:npx packed the current tree, installed it into a fresh temporary project, exercised the CLI and all 13 bundled packages, and cleaned the sandbox successfully (version 2026.7.21)."
  "2026-07-21T10:47:25.985Z",codex-root-20260721,"Final exact-commit Greptile review scored 5/5 with no comments, but noted a soft resolver/validator contract gap for empty or leading-dot inputs. Tightening the public resolver invariant before push."
  "2026-07-21T10:52:29.795Z",codex-root-20260721,"Greptile contract remediation verified: resolver now trims empty versions to development and rewrites a leading dot, so every generated token is accepted by pruning; scoped, empty, dot-prefixed, and traversal-shaped cases are covered. Full 6053-test suite remains exact 100/100/100/100."
